CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 25, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Housing Board Member - When the Rev. Charles H. Foggie, center, minister of Wesley Center AME Zion Church, was sworn in as member of the Pittsburgh Housing Authority Monday to replace Atty. Richard F. Jones, who retired last October, on hand to greet him were Atty. Everette [sic] Utterback, Housing Authority counsel; Mrs. Foggie, his wife; Alfred Tronzo, deputy administrator, and Councilman Paul F. Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence swearing in Charles H. Foggie to member of Pittsburgh Housing Authority, with Madeline Sharpe Foggie in between them, in mayor's office
